Jeff Wicks, News24Snake catcher Garth Carpenter with the 3m-long black mamba he caught on a KZN farm. (The Witness) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - An eight-year-old girl is in a serious condition in a Pietermaritzburg hospital after she was bitten by a Night Adder in Northdale on Sunday. Netcare911 spokesperson Chris Botha said medics had received a report of the emergency and rushed to the scene. &ldquo;Reports indicate that she was walking along the driveway when the snake bit her on the foot,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;Paramedics found the girl at her home with swelling and pain to the bite site. A neighbour found the snake under some rocks and killed it."Botha said paramedics identified the snake as a Night Adder.After treating the girl at the scene they transported her to a local hospital. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.